rom the Hindu-Brahmin Chakra system but reconfigured into a nine-center model that Ra Uru Hu described as reflecting the post-1781 mutation in human consciousness (the year Uranus was discovered, marking what Human Design calls the shift from a seven-center to a nine-center being).\n[...]\n## The 64 Gates\n[...]\nGates are the numbered entry and exit points on each Center. There are 64 of them in total, corresponding directly to the 64 hexagrams of the I Ching — the ancient Chinese Book of Changes. Each Gate carries the archetypal theme of its I Ching hexagram, translated into the Human Design context.\n[...]\nA Gate becomes active in your chart when a planet occupies that position at either your birth time (Conscious layer) or approximately 88 days before your birth (Unconscious layer). An active Gate creates a consistent energy theme associated with that Gate's archetype.\n[...]\n## The 36 Channels\n[...]\nA Channel forms when two Gates — one on each end of a Channel connection — are both active. When a Channel is complete, it connects two Centers, and energy flows between those Centers consistently. A defined Channel is what makes Centers Defined: a Center is colored in only when at least one Channel running into or out of it is fully activated.\n[...]\nThere are 36 Channels in the BodyGraph, each with its own name and archetypal theme based on the two Gates it combines. Channels are grouped into three circuit types — Individual, Tribal, and Collective — reflecting different modes of energy flow and purpose.\n[...]\nCheck your Profile — derived from the line numbers next to your Conscious and Unconscious Sun gates (the numbers after the decimal in the Gate/Line notation).\n\n---\n\nTitle: How to Read Your Human Design Bodygraph: A Step-by-Step Beginner's Guide | Human Design Blog – Articles, Guides & Insights\nURL: https://humandesignchart.org/blog/how-to-read-human-design-bodygraph\nPublished: 2026-04-04T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe bodygraph is 