 mind instead of your body — Authority lives in the body, never in the mental conclusion\n- ❌ Looking for instant transformation — Ra Uru Hu suggested a 7-year experiment before you judge the system\n- ❌ Mixing Human Design with other systems too soon — learn the mechanics on their own terms first\n[...]\n- What is Human Design?— The history, theory, and synthesis\n- The 5 Energy Types— Quick test for your Type\n- Ra Uru Hu: The Founder of Human Design— Where this system came from\n- Understanding Double Activation Signals— Why some channels look red-and-black striped\n- Quantum Human Design Explained— A modern re-languaging of the original material\n- Human Design vs Astrology— How they overlap and where they diverge\n\n---\n\nTitle: Human Design Chart: How to Read Your BodyGraph\nURL: https://thalira.com/blogs/quantum-codex/human-design-chart-explained\nPublished: 2026-03-24T03:33:59.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nYour Human Design chart (BodyGraph) maps 9 energy centres, 36 channels, and 64 gates calculated from your birth date, time, and location. Start reading your chart with Type (your aura mechanics), then Strategy (how to make correct decisions), then Authority (which body intelligence to trust). Defined (coloured) areas are your consistent energy; open (white) areas are where you absorb and amplify others.\n[...]\nThe BodyGraph is the central visual tool of the Human Design system. It is a schematic diagram of the human energy field, showing 9 geometric shapes (centres) connected by 36 lines (channels), with 64 numbered points (gates) distributed across those channels and centres. When calculated for a specific individual using their birth data, the BodyGraph reveals a unique pattern of defined and undefined elements that constitutes their energetic design.\n[...]\nRa Uru Hu received the Human Design system in January 1987, and the BodyGraph is his synthesis of four ancient knowledge systems:\n[...]\n- The I Ching provides the 64 gates (hexagrams) and the 6 lines within each gate.\n[...]\n- The Kabbalistic Tree of Life provides the structural layout of the centres and the pathways (channels) between them. The BodyGraph's nine centres correspond to the Sephiroth, adapted from the original Hermetic and Kabbalistic framework.\n- The Hindu-Brahmin chakra system provides the original energy centre concept, which Ra updated from seven centres to nine for the current era.\n- Western astrology provides the planetary activation mechanism: the positions of the Sun, Moon, and planets at specific moments determine which gates are activated in your chart.\n[...]\n## The 36 Channels\n[...]\nby any combination\n[...]\nthe 64 hexagram\n[...]\ncorrespondence is direct\n[...]\n64 (\n[...]\n, corresponding to the\n[...]\nof the I Ching hexagram.\n[...]\nis determined by the exact degree of the planet activating that gate. The\n[...]\nadds nuance to the gate'\n[...]\ntheme: Line 1 is investigative (foundation-building),\n[...]\nis hermit-like (natural talent), Line 3 is experimental (trial and error), Line 4 is social (networking and influence), Line\n[...]\nis universalising (projection and heresy), and Line 6 is transcendent (role model after maturity).\n[...]\nA Human Design chart (BodyGraph) is a visual map of your energetic blueprint, calculated from your exact birth date, time, and location. It shows 9 energy centres, 36 channels, and 64 gates, along with your type, strategy, authority, profile, and incarnation cross.\n[...]\nA channel connects two centres via two activated gates. There are 36 channels. A defined channel creates consistent energy flow between the connected centres, with a specific theme from its I Ching hexagram components.","_meta":{"searchTime":1283.2}}]}
